== DHKE
- Alice selects a random $x_A in {0, ..., p-2}$, Bob $x_B$
- Alice calculates $y_A = R_p (g^(x_A))$, Bob $y_B = R_p (g^(x_B))$
- They exchange $y_A, y_B$
- Alice calculates $k_(A B) = R_p (y_B^(x_A))$, Bob $k_(B A) = R_p (y_A^(x_B))$
Now, they have $k_(A B) equiv y_B^(x_A) equiv (g^(x_B))^(x_A) equiv g^(x_A x_B) equiv k_(B A)$

*Example*
Using $chevron.l 2 chevron.r in chevron.l ZZ^*_15; dot.o chevron.r$ ($g=2$). $y_A=8, k_(A B)=2$. Find $y_B$.

$
  8 = R_15 (2^(x_A)) ==> x_A = 3 ==> 2^(3 x_B) equiv_15 2 ==> 8^(x_B) equiv_15 2 ==> x_B=3 ==> y_B=R_15 (2^3)=8
$
